---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Checkout Ninja"
  description="Terms of Service for Checkout Ninja by Nex App Studio. Read the terms governing use of our Shopify Plus checkout customization app."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="pt-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Last updated: March 7, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="pb-16 lg:pb-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-gray prose-headings:font-heading prose-headings:font-semibold prose-a:text-mint-500 hover:prose-a:text-mint-600">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Checkout Ninja app ("the App") provided by Nex App Studio ("we", "us", "our"). By installing or using the App, you agree to these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Checkout Ninja is a Shopify app that enables checkout customization for Shopify Plus stores.</li>
          <li>By installing the app, you agree to be bound by these Terms.</li>
          <li>You must have a valid Shopify Plus store to use the App.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Use of the App</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You may use the App to customize your Shopify checkout as intended.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for the content you add to your checkout (blocks, messages, custom fields).</li>
          <li>You must not use the App for any illegal or unauthorized purpose.</li>
          <li>You must not misuse the App in ways that could harm other merchants or Shopify's platform.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Account & Access</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Access to the App is managed through your Shopify store account.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your Shopify account.</li>
          <li>You must be authorized to act on behalf of the store installing the App.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Pricing & Billing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Pricing is as listed on the Shopify App Store and our pricing page.</li>
          <li>Billing is handled through Shopify's billing system.</li>
          <li>All plans include a 3-day free trial.</li>
          <li>Annual plans are billed upfront and save 17% compared to monthly billing.</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days notice.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Cancellation & Refunds</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can cancel your subscription at any time by uninstalling the App from your Shopify store.</li>
          <li>Cancellation takes effect at the end of your current billing period.</li>
          <li>Refund requests are handled on a case-by-case basis — contact <a href="mailto:support@nexappstudio.com">support@nexappstudio.com</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Certain features (API validation, address validation, gift card validation) connect to external services configured by you.</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for the availability, accuracy, or performance of third-party services.</li>
          <li>You are responsible for complying with the terms of any third-party service you connect.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The App, including its design, code, and documentation, is owned by Nex App Studio.</li>
          <li>You retain ownership of any content you create using the App (block configurations, custom text, images).</li>
          <li>You may not copy, modify, or distribute the App or its code.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind.</li>
          <li>We are not liable for any lost revenue, data loss, or damages arising from use of the App.</li>
          <li>Our total liability is limited to the amount you paid for the App in the last 12 months.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Service Availability</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We aim to keep the App available at all times but cannot guarantee uninterrupted service.</li>
          <li>We may perform maintenance or updates that temporarily affect availability.</li>
          <li>We will provide notice of planned maintenance where possible.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We may update these Terms from time to time.</li>
          <li>We will notify merchants of significant changes via email.</li>
          <li>Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>These Terms are governed by the laws of the United Arab Emirates.</li>
          <li>Any disputes will be resolved in the courts of Sharjah, UAE.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these Terms, contact us at: <a href="mailto:support@nexappstudio.com">support@nexappstudio.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>Nex App Studio, Sharjah, UAE</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
